ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It is good and necessary! I would recommend it to other students.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: It gave me more exposure to laboratory techniques, experience with experimental analysis and time with different PIs and lab members.

During my rotation, I learned many new research techniques and became familiar with a new model organism. My rotation definitely deepened my knowledge of research in general and in the context of the lab's specific area of research.
I loved my first rotation. It was a great experience and will help me decide what lab I want to be in. Also, the results in the lab helped me greatly with my NSF proposal.

The lab rotations gave us the chance to experience in different labs before we find the one in which we are going to finish our graduate thesis. Also, we can learn different techniques in different labs.
